<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblecharknown" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Illegible Characters, Quantity Known</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>Where vestiges of characters remain, but they cannot be recognised and their quantity is
        known, they should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> and given a <att>reason</att>
        with a value of "illegible".</p>

    <cit>
        <!-- VIII.2 is a normal gap (characters lost, lacuna) - there is no Panciera section corresponding exactly to 'Illegible Characters, Quantity Known' but I think this would be rendered the same way -->
        <quote>[...]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera">
            <biblScope>VIII.2</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="3" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://irt.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT690.html">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="ddbdp" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;1;101"> 
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="2" unit="character"/>
    </egXML>

    <div xml:id="trans-illegiblecharknown-responsibility">

        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Scott Vanderbilt</name>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt></bibl>
            <bibl><respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Charlotte Tupman</name>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt></bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
